article.headline: Sam Houston St. 71, Cent. Arkansas 55
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Ryan Bright had 14 points and 14 rebounds to lead Sam Houston State to 71-55 win over Central Arkansas on Saturday. John Gardiner also had 15 points for the Bearkats (19-5, 7-4 Southland Conference.) Nate Bowie led Central Arkansas (13-12, 3-8) with 17 points. The Bears held a 1-point lead at halftime, but shot just 9-of-28 in the second half, compared with the Bearkats' 15-of-26. Sam Houston State's largest lead was 18 points, with 1:28 remaining. DeLuis Ramirez and Ashton Mitchell each added 11 points for Sam Houston State. Durell Nevels had 12 points and 11 rebounds for Central Arkansas.
